title: Mavin Future Five
description:
#mavin #futurefive

To apply: www.mavinrecords.com

The Mavin Future Five is a unique 6 months program that will give profound working experience in the music industry to 5 young graduates. They will receive mentorship from the Mavin team as they grow and evolve during the internship. As a member of our team, you will work on specific tasks critical to the label’s needs. 

Artists Relations Intern: Artist Development, Publishing, Sync Licensing Catalog

Digital Intern: Data Analysis, DSP Profiling, Playlisting, Music Technology, Web Development & CRM

New Business Intern: Brand Activations, Touring, Artist Management, Merch, Innovative Products, Partnerships

Creative Marketing Intern: Email Marketing, Social Media, Branding, Content Development, Influencer Marketing, 

Promotions & Publicity Intern: TV, Radio, Clubs, Press, Audience Development

title: Johnny Drille - Papa ( Official Music Video )
description:
‘Papa’ is Johnny Drille’s most personal and emotionally driven song to date. A poignant ode to fathers, the lyrics tackle his feelings of missing home after leaving his hometown of Benin City for Lagos as he reflects on how his father’s wisdom continues to guide him.

title: Welcome To Mavin Records: Crayon
description:
Don Jazzy’s Mavin Records Signs New Artist Crayon; launches BLOWTIME imprint with Producer Baby Fresh

Mavin Records announces the signing of Crayon, the first artist signed to Baby Fresh’s Blowtime Entertainment record label imprint. Crayon’s innovative music blends global pop, local Afrobeats, Latin and Caribbean rhythms for a dynamic new sound with mass appeal.


“We are pleased to announce our new imprint deal with Baby Fresh's Blowtime Entertainment as we unveil our new artist, Crayon. Baby Fresh has always been part of the Mavin family and we look forward to what is shaping up to be a remarkable stage of his amazing career. Crayon is an exceptional songwriter and recording artist who comes with a lot of diversity in his music and I am sure that we will attain great things together,” said Don Jazzy, Mavin’s founder and President.

“Crayon is a bundle of talent and creating this imprint with Baby Fresh is part of our objective to deliver dynamic growth for our artists. Our ambition is to help talent achieve their musical and entrepreneurial goals with our infrastructure, unique experience and diverse team. This kind of collaboration is vital for the growth of our industry,” said Mavin’s COO, Tega Oghenejobo.

Crayon grew up in Iba, Lagos, filling notebooks with lyrics and jumping at the first chance he got to record in a studio, where he met his friend and collaborator Ozedikus. By chance, Baby Fresh heard one of those early songs and instantly knew Crayon had potential to become the new face and voice of Afrobeats. 

“He’s called Crayon because his work is so colorful: it channels Fela, Drake, Justin Bieber, Bryson Tiller, Wizkid and Davido in a way that feels completely current and fresh. I was on the lookout for a new artist to take Afrobeats somewhere newer and bigger, and that’s what I found in him,” Baby Fresh said. 

“I want to put my community on the map. I’ll be the first artist to really break out of Iba, and that means a lot to me. When I started making music I was just a kid. I’m crazy excited to share my music and be part of this moment when Afrobeats are going global,” Crayon said. 

Crayon will be featured on several upcoming releases from fellow Mavins and his own EP will debut this summer. Follow him on Instagram at @crayonthis and follow @mavinrecords for updates on new releases and signings.

title: Welcome Rema
description:
Mavin Records and Jonzing World present the breakthrough teenage artist Rema, unveiling his debut EP 'Rema' - packed with infectious afrobeat grooves and released via Mavin Records as part of their first imprint deal.

Rema is a fantastic example of the strength of talent currently emerging from Africa, with 'Iron Man' a superb introduction that is likely to gain him many plaudits. His ability to confidently navigate his way throughout the project belies his 18 years, merely scratching the surface of his undoubted potential.

“Rema is a formidable young artist: with his skill and versatility, he has a unique place in the future of afrobeats. At the same time, we’re excited to launch our first imprint deal with Jonzing World. This model will expand the number of ways the Mavin platform can support artists and entrepreneurship in Africa to grow together, at home and internationally, ” said D on Jazzy, Mavin Global President.

The Nigerian artist honed his musical skills and individual sound in church and in the playgrounds of Benin City as a young teen, often drawing crowds that were willing to pay to see him perform popular songs. Since then, with the help of Mavin Global & Jonzing World, his reputation has grown and that's likely to be the case for years to come, with label head & visionary Don Jazzy also aiding the careers of Tiwa Savage, Korede Bello, Dr Sid, Johnny Drille, Di'Ja, D'Prince, LADIPOE, DJ Big N and DNA through their work with Mavin.

Rema himself believes "It still feels like a blessing to be chosen for something great, something beyond this world” as he aims to inspire other young people through his music.

'Rema' is available now on all streaming platform at http://bit.ly/rema-is-on

Tracklist:
1 Iron Man
2 Corny
3 Dumebi
4 Why

title: D'Prince - Gucci Gang (feat. Davido & Don Jazzy) [ Official Audio & Lyrics Video ]
description:
D'Prince - Gucci Gang (feat. Davido & Don Jazzy) [ Lyrics Video ]. 

Download MP3 of Gucci Gang at http://bit.ly/guccigang-mp3-download

Stream Gucci Gang at http://bit.ly/dprince-guccigang

This collaboration was a long time coming between the Mavin superstar and DMW superstar.

Davido's rise to fame was inspired partly by the legendary hits of D'Prince such as Give It To Me and Take Banana.

The admiration and respect both artists have for each other led to their first collaboration in 2014 titled Gentlemen, produced by Don Jazzy.

In 2017, both artists saw active campaigns with D’Prince releasing song that included So Nice ft. Wizkid, Guys and Sade while Davido released songs that included IF, Fall and FIA. As both artists embark on their 2018 campaigns,  Gucci Gang will sure be one of the key songs for both artists.

title: Godwyn ft. Di'Ja - Promise music video
description: The incredible journey of Godwyn continues. This amazing guitarist was discovered by Don Jazzy on Instagram last year when Don Jazzy saw Godwyn's guitar playing Instagram videos. Within 24 hours of this discovery, the opportunistic Godwyn made his way to Mavin studios where he recorded Promise with Don Jazzy and Di'Ja. Don Jazzy released this song and it helped change Godwyn's life, earning him national exposure which led to performances all over Lagos. Today, we release the music video of this beautiful song. Godwyn's story is an inspiring one that teaches us the following: If you have great talent and you put it out there in unique ways and are opportunistic, great things will eventually happen to you.
caption: false

title: Mavins  - JantaManta Official Music Video
description:
The Supreme Mavin Dynasty presents the music video of JantaManta, a new magical single featuring Don Jazzy, Tiwa Savage, Dr.Sid, D'Prince, Di'Ja, Reekado Banks and Korede Bello. It is produced by Don Jazzy.

The magic began 4 months ago when Don Jazzy previewed the early beginning of JantaManta on Instagram and Snapchat. After perfecting the beat, the 6 dynamic and award winning Mavin Record artistes proceeded to add their creative lyrics to bring the song to life. 
JantaManta is the 4th single from the Mavins after the groundbreaking Dorobucci, Adaobi and Looku Looku.


Below are the lyrics:

[Chorus – Don Jazzy]
Jantamanta kilanja kabakaba ah
Eh Jantamanta kabakaba

See this young girl passing by

I go form a militant
I go bomb your heart ah

I go form a carpenter

title: D'Prince ft. Phyno - Tarity Official Music Video
description:
Take a journey and experience the beautiful eastern culture of Nigeria with D’Prince and Phyno with this massively heavy tune titled Tarity.

The music video is a flawless depiction of the flagship unique Odumodu dance and the iconic Ekpo masquerade from the ancestral Igbo heartland of Umuahia, Abia state. 

The touch of classic Mercedes Benzs and Lebron's add rich and colorful dynamics that give this music video a vintage but yet contemporary feel.; all while enhancing the arts and cultural values of Nigeria. 

This spectacular music video is directed by Don Lulu Films.


About D’Prince 
D’Prince, one of Mavin Records finest,  is currently on a hit-release spree. Tarity is his 3rd music video release in the past two months. It follows the hilariously successful Oga Titus and Bestie, the new #FriendZone anthem. D’Prince is on Twitter and Instagram with the @dprincemavin handle.

Subscribe to your YouTube channel to get notified when we release new videos: http://bit.ly/mavinyoutubesubscribe

description:
The Supreme Mavin Dynasty presents JantaManta, a new magical single featuring Don Jazzy, Tiwa Savage, Dr.Sid, D'Prince, Di'Ja, Reekado Banks and Korede Bello. It is produced by Don Jazzy.

The magic began 3 months ago when Don Jazzy previewed the early beginning of JantaManta on Instagram and Snapchat. After perfecting the beat, the 6 dynamic and award winning Mavin Record artistes proceeded to add their creative lyrics to bring the song to life. 
JantaManta is the 4th single from the Mavins after the groundbreaking Dorobucci, Adaobi and Looku Looku.

title: D'Prince - OYO ( On Your Own )
description:
In a world of 7.2 billion people, a league of united nations and powerful government organizations, D'Prince takes a stab at reality with a simple message "You are on your own". 
Arguably one of Don Jazzy's finest production yet. O.Y.O (On Your Own) is a brand new Afrobeat inspired single from D'Prince.

O.Y.O is a wake up call to each and every one of us who have grown comfortable with the idea of building our personal hustle around other people who are occupied with their own hustle; it's time to start fighting for yourself.

In many ways O.Y.O is also a warning to those few among us who hardly care about the rest of us; when the proverbial shit hits the fan (as it usually does), you my dear will be packing it on your own. Enjoy!

Download at http://bit.ly/DprinceOYO

title: Industry Nite With The Mavins
description:
Lagos came to a standstill on Wednesday night as the Mavins shut down Industry Nite. A jam-packed Oriental Hotel played host to hundreds of fans and celebrities who all came to see the Mavins perform together for the first time. And what a performance it was! Wande Coal, Tiwa Savage, Dr.Sid, D' Prince and Don Jazzy all took turns to individually and collectively wow the crowd .

The Mavins performance was the climax of a night that saw other artists such as Segun and Yemi Alade take to the stage. There was also a joint performance between Tunde Ednut and Dr.Sid for 'Catching Cold' which brought the house down. It was a night full of light hearted fun with even Don Jazzy taking to the stage to do the Azonto with Wande Coal. The Mavin crew thanked all their fans who were able to make it and promised that there is much more to come from the label.

www.mavinrecords.com

Follow @mavinrecords @donjazzy @iamdrsid @dprincemavin @tiwasavage @wandecoal on twitter

Join the mavin league: www.mavinrecords.com/league
